{{Infobox language |name=Esmeralda |altname=Atacame |nativename=Takame |familycolor=American |states=[[Ecuador]] |extinct=? |fam1=[[Esmeralda–Yaruro languages|Esmeralda–Yaruro]] ? |iso3=none |glotto=atac1235 |glottorefname=Atacame }}
'''Esmeralda''', or ''Esmeraldeño'' (also called ''Takame'' or ''Atacame''), is an [[extinct language|extinct]] [[language isolate]] formerly spoken in the coastal region of [[Ecuador]]. It has been proposed that the language is connected to the still-spoken [[Yaruro language]] of [[Venezuela]]. It also has some lexical similarities with the extinct [[Yurumanguí language]].<ref name="Cambridge">{{cite book | last1 = Adelaar| first1 = William F. H. | last2 = Muysken | first2 = Pieter C.| authorlink = | coauthors = | title = The languages of the Andes| publisher = Cambridge University Press| series = Cambridge Language Surveys| volume = | edition = | date = 2004| location = | pages = 156–161| language = | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UiwaUY6KsY8C&pg=PA34&lpg=PA34&dq=The+languages+of+the+andes+esmeralda&source=bl&ots=FdhFLjCyTA&sig=nR7vos_UJFaGCPXh-spZNGsAF6k&hl=en&sa=X&ei=12UuU8ONCZOskAeLjoAQ&ved=0CEUQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=Esmeralde%CB%9Cno&f=false| doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
