{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Kirovske |native_name = Кіровське |other_name = Кировское |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_flag = File:Flag of Khrestivka.svg |image_shield = File:Kirovske gerb.png |shield_size = |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{UKR}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Oblast]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Donetsk Oblast]] |leader_title = Mayor |leader_name = Larysa Hrechushkina (interim) |established_title = Founded |established_date = 1954 |established_title1 = City status |established_date1 = 1987 |area_total_km2 = 7,25 |population_as_of = 2014 |population_total = 28149 |population_density_km2 = 3882 |timezone = EET |utc_offset = +2 |timezone_DST = EEST |utc_offset_DST = +3 |postal_code_type = Postal code |postal_code = 86300-86390 |website = |footnotes = }} '''Kirovske''' ({{lang-uk|Кіровське}}, {{lang-ru|Кировское}}) is a [[City of regional significance (Ukraine)|city of oblast significance]] in [[Donetsk Oblast]] ([[oblast|province]]) of [[Ukraine]]. Population: {{Ua-pop-est2013|28,291}}; 30,910 (2001).
On 14 April 2014 [[2014 pro-Russian conflict in Ukraine|pro-Russian activists]] captured Kirovske's town hall and declared that the city was part of the [[2014 insurgency in Donbass|separatist]] [[Donetsk Peoples Republic]].<ref>{{ru icon}} [http://kp.ua/politics/448322-chastui-donetskoi-narodnoi-respublyky-staly-zhdanovka-y-kyrovskoe As part of the People's Republic of Donetsk steel Zhdanovka and Kirov [map]], [[Komsomolskaya Pravda in Ukraine]] (14 April 2014)</ref> Since then the city stayed under separatist control.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/ioana-moldovan-/ukraine-idps-photos_b_7899752.html When Ukraine Is No Longer Ukraine], [[The Huffington Post]] (29 July 2015)</ref>
